 WEEKLY\nWRESTLING MATCHES\nPOSTPONED A WEEK\nRegular Card Monday, Dec. 6th,\nat Miners Union Hall.\nDue to so many of the boys going\nhome for the holidays, the Pioneer\nAthletic Club have decided to give\nthe hundreds of wrestling fans a one\nweek rest from the greatest sport\nin the world.\nStatistics prove there are more\npeople attending the wrestling\nmatches than any other attraction,\neven football. In thousands of cities\nthere are wrestling matches going\non each night.\nFor the December 6th card, the\nmatchmaker is trying to get King\nKong Clayton, the colored boy who\nmade such a hit here, matched with\nBilly Spendlove. Should these two\nboys agree to terms, etc., the bout\nshould be a thriller.\nSo far no negotiations are out for\nthe other bouts, but as soon as the\nmain event is lined up the balance\nof the bouts will be arranged.\nFortune Teller: You will die on a\nJewish holiday, mein Fuehrer.\nHitler; Ach! On a Jewish holiday?\nWhich one?\nFortune Teller: I don't know. Any\nday you die will be a Jewish holiday.\nIndependently Owned and Operated\n\u2022Jil i\n.11\nTHURSDAY-FRIDAY\nNov. 25-26\nIT HAPPENED ONE\nNIGHT\"\nWith CLARK GABLE and\nCLAUDETTE COLBERT\nSILLY SYMPHONY CARTOON\nNEWS NOVELTY\nSATURDAY\nNov. 27\nSCOTT COLTON and\nJEAN ROGERS in\n'THE WILDCATTER\"\nComedy Cartoon News Novelty\nand the Last Episode of\n\"THE CLUTCHING HAND'\u00bb\nKiddies Matinee\u20141 to 5 o'clock\u20145c\nSTARTING SUNDAY\nNov. 28\n100 MEN AND A GIRL\"\nWith DEANNA DURBIN and\nA. MENJOU\nMickey Mouse Cartoon News\nusa\nA Heat buy in\nCALIFORNIA WINE\nV\n\nW\\\n20\nalcohol\nBY VOLUME Sr~.\nm mi\nv\ngj\nRi\n>7\nPORT WIN\u00ab\nT\nIfcj\n\nKB","height":"19596","width":"14331"}}
